# III. Global Blockchain Adoption (2026)

## 1. Global Adoption by People

### User Base

- Around 283 million people use blockchain worldwide
- Represents approximately 3.9 % of the global population

### Regional Adoption

- Asia: ~160 million users (largest share)
- Europe and North America: Millions of users
- Oceania: ~1 million users

Blockchain adoption remains at an early stage globally.

---

## 2. Enterprise and Business Adoption

### Business Engagement

- Nearly 90 % of enterprises report using or planning blockchain adoption
- Considered a strategic technology across industries

### Industry Applications

Blockchain is used in:

- Supply chain tracking
- Payments and remittances
- Healthcare data security
- Real estate and ownership records
- Government and public services

---

## 3. Blockchain Market and Growth Trends

### Market Value

- USD 31–40 billion in 2025
- Estimated USD 39.8 billion in 2026
- Expected to reach hundreds of billions by 2030

### Growth Rate (CAGR)

- Projected annual growth: 60–90 %
- Driven by enterprise and institutional adoption

---

## 4. Sector-Wise Adoption Trends (2026)

### Financial Services

- Strong adoption in fintech and payments
- Tokenization and cross-border transfers expanding
- 76 % of global investors plan to increase digital asset exposure

### Enterprise Systems

- Used for asset tracking and smart contract automation
- Over 80 % of companies report direct or planned blockchain usage

### Supply Chain and Logistics

- Improves traceability and transparency
- Reduces operational costs

---

## 5. Emerging Global Trends (2026)

### Institutional Adoption

- Traditional finance increasingly uses blockchain
- Includes debt issuance and regulated stablecoins

### Tokenization of Assets

- Real-world assets such as bonds and real estate are tokenized
- Expands blockchain use beyond payments

---

## Key Percentage Highlights (2026)

| Metric                               | Approximate Value |
|-------------------------------------|------------------|
| Global population using blockchain  | ~3.9 % (~283 million) |
| Enterprises adopting blockchain     | ~90 % |
| Projected CAGR                      | ~60–90 % |
| Market value by 2030                | Hundreds of billions to over $1 trillion |

---

## Summary (Exam-Ready)

As of 2026, blockchain adoption among individuals remains limited at about 3.9 % of the global population, while enterprise adoption is very high at nearly 90 %. Blockchain is widely used in payments, supply chains, data security, and asset tokenization, with strong market growth and increasing institutional participation.
